<TITLE> CA awards national sports prizes </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, April 08 (bdnews24.com)Chief adviser Fakhruddin Ahmed handed the National Sports Award 2007 to ten sporting personalities Tuesday at the Osmani Memorial Auditorium. The national award, introduced in 1976, has been conferred upon the ten deserving sportsmen and women for various achievements past and present in different fields. The award-winners for 2007 are: Sharmila Roy (athletics), Ranjit Das (football), Amir Hossain Patwari (kabadi), Lt Comm (retd) M Arshad (swimming), Aminul Islam (judo), Nurul Islam (hockey), Abul Hashem (badminton), Prof Rashiduddin Ahmad (basketball), Kazi Anisur Rahman (organiser) and Ataul Haque Mallick (organiser-posthumous). The chief adviser awarded the ten winners with crests and cash cheques. He called upon Bangladeshis to revive sports at all levels across the country. Fakhruddin also urged all to work towards a drug-free nation through the regular practice of sports. bdnews24.com
